# Passport — core rules

Follow [ARCHITECTURE.md](../../ARCHITECTURE.md) and [`docs/domain-specification.md`](../../docs/domain-specification.md).

## Stack

- Quarkus + REST/JSON. PostgreSQL + Flyway. SmallRye JWT.
- Mailer for password reset (`MailerService`, CDI events).
- Repo tooling: no Python — [passport-tooling-languages.mdc](passport-tooling-languages.mdc).

## Endpoints

- `@Path` + constructor injection. Records for request/response bodies.
- Admin APIs: `@RolesAllowed(RequiredRoles.ADMIN)` → `passport.admin`.
- Auth routes public where appropriate (`/auth/login`, reset flow).

## Data access

- Repositories in feature packages; `EntityManager`; `@Transactional` on writes.
- [passport-jpa.mdc](passport-jpa.mdc) for query style.
- Password hashing only via `PasswordEncoder`; JWT via `JwtGenerator`.

## Never

- `System.out.println` — use SLF4J.
- Return raw encoded passwords in API responses.
- Hardcode role strings in many places — use seeds / `RequiredRoles` / domain spec.

## When adding a feature

ARCHITECTURE.md §13 — migration → model → repository → endpoint → tests → dev seed → domain spec → **ARCHITECTURE.md**.
